  "prompt": "How do I pass CA IPCC in 10 days?",
  "response": "Passing CA IPCC (now called CA Intermediate) in just 10 days is extremely challenging and not recommended. However, here are some intense study strategies:\n\n1. Study Plan:\n- Create a strict, disciplined study schedule\n- Study 12-16 hours daily\n- Focus on high-weightage topics\n- Prioritize important chapters\n\n2. Study Techniques:\n- Use revision notes and summaries\n- Practice previous years' question papers\n- Take mock tests\n- Focus on understanding concepts, not just memorizing\n- Use mnemonic techniques\n\n3. Subject-wise Preparation:\n- Group 1: Accounting, Law, Business Communication\n- Group 2: Advanced Accounting, Taxation, Auditing, etc.\n\n4. Recommended Resources:\n- ICAI study materials\n- Suggested practice manuals\n- Online video lectures\n- Quick revision books\n\n5. Exam Strategy:\n- Solve maximum possible question papers\n- Practice time management\n- Focus on attempting all questions\n- Learn marking schemes\n\n6. Additional Tips:\n- Stay physically and mentally healthy\n- Take short breaks\n- Stay hydrated\n- Get minimal sleep (4-6 hours)\n\nDisclaimer: 10 days is extremely short. Ideally, prepare for 3-6 months.",
